alcatelIND1StackMgrMIB.name: alcatelIND1StackMgrMIB

revisions.description: Added alaStackMgrOperStackingMode and alaStackMgrAdminStackingMode objects. Added AlaStackMgrStackingMode TEXTUAL-CONVENTION.
New trap alaStackMgrBadMixTrap has been added. AlaStackMgrSlotState & AlaStackMgrLinkNumber textual convention have been modified.
Updates on definitions for link states. Updates on pass through slot range.
New trap alaStackMgrOutOfPassThruSlotsTrap has been added.
alaStackMgrPassThruTrap has been split in three traps to assure backwards compatibility with previous releases of the Birds Of Prey products.
-Command action and command status objects added to the chassis table. -Link state textual conventions have been updated.
Objects to handle information about token usage.
Objects to support the pass through mode added.

AlaStackMgrLinkNumber.name: AlaStackMgrLinkNumber
AlaStackMgrLinkNumber.description: Lists the port numbers that the stackable ports can hold. Also the values are the same as the one marked on the Stack chassis pannel. These values are hardware dependent as follows: - First generation stackable switches - 24 ports: linkA27=27, linkB28=28, - First generation stackable switches - 48 ports: linkA51=51, linkB52=52, - 1st version of 2nd generation stackable switches : linkA31=31, linkB32=32. - 2nd version of 2nd generation stackable switches 24-port : linkA25=25, linkB26=26, - 2nd version of 2nd generation stackable switches 48-port : linkA29=29, linkB30=30.

AlaStackMgrNINumber.name: AlaStackMgrNINumber
AlaStackMgrNINumber.description: The numbers allocated for the stack NIs are as follows: - 0 = invalid slot number; - 1..8 = valid and assigned slot numbers corresponding values from the entPhysicalTable; - 1001..1008 = switches operating in pass through mode; - 255 = unassigned slot number.

AlaStackMgrLinkStatus.name: AlaStackMgrLinkStatus
AlaStackMgrLinkStatus.description: Provides the logical stack link status. The logical link is considered operational if the physical link is operational and communication with the adjacent switch is active. The possible values are: - up(1), - down(2).

AlaStackMgrSlotRole.name: AlaStackMgrSlotRole
AlaStackMgrSlotRole.description: Indicates the role of each switch within the stack as follows: - unassigned(0), - primary(1), - secondary(2), - idle(3), - standalone(4), - passthrough(5)

AlaStackMgrStackStatus.name: AlaStackMgrStackStatus
AlaStackMgrStackStatus.description: Indicates whether the stack ring is or not in loop as follows: - loop(1), - noloop(2)

AlaStackMgrSlotState.name: AlaStackMgrSlotState
AlaStackMgrSlotState.description: Current operational state of a stack element as follows: - running(1) : switch is fully operational, - duplicateSlot(2): switch operates in pass through mode due to slot duplication, - clearedSlot(3) : switch operates in pass through mode upon management command, - outOfSlots(4) : switch operates in pass through because the maximum number of allowed stackable swicthes has been reached, - outOfTokens(5) : switch operates in pass through mode because no tokens are available to be assigned. - badMix (6) : switch operates in pass through mode because it's not compatible with the existing stack.

AlaStackMgrCommandAction.name: AlaStackMgrCommandAction
AlaStackMgrCommandAction.description: Identifies which of the following actions is to be performed: - notSiginificant(0) : no action, - clearSlot(1) : saved slot number will be removed from persistent database, - clearSlotImmediately : saved slot number will be cleared and change will be in effect right away causing the switch to enter in pass through mode, - reloadAny(3) : reboot an element regardless of its operational mode, - reloadPassThru(4) : reboot an element that is operating in pass thru mode.

AlaStackMgrCommandStatus.name: AlaStackMgrCommandStatus
AlaStackMgrCommandStatus.description: Identifies the current status of the last action command received as follows: - notSignificant(0), - clearSlotInProgress(1), - clearSlotFailed(2), - clearSlotSuccess(3), - setSlotInProgress(4), - setSlotFailed(5), - setSlotSuccess(6).

AlaStackMgrStackingMode.name: AlaStackMgrStackingMode
AlaStackMgrStackingMode.description: Stacking mode, which specifies the ability of a switch to be part of a set of switches or virtual chassis: - stackable(1) :the switch may be stacked with other switches in the same virtual chassis. - standalone(2) :the switch is not allowed to be stacked together with other switches.

alaStackMgrChassisTable.name: alaStackMgrChassisTable
alaStackMgrChassisTable.description: Maintains a list with information about all the switches that participate on the stack herein refered to as chassis.

alaStackMgrChassisEntry.name: alaStackMgrChassisEntry
alaStackMgrChassisEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to a chassis and lists its role and neighbors in the stack.

alaStackMgrSlotNINumber.name: alaStackMgrSlotNINumber
alaStackMgrSlotNINumber.description: Numbers allocated for the stack NIs as follows: - 0: invalid slot number - 1..8: valid and assigned slot numbers corresponding to values from the entPhysicalTable - 1001..1008: swicthes operating in pass through mode - 255: unassigned slot number.

alaStackMgrSlotCMMNumber.name: alaStackMgrSlotCMMNumber
alaStackMgrSlotCMMNumber.description: The numbers allocated for the stack CMMs are from 65..72 or 0 if not present

alaStackMgrChasRole.name: alaStackMgrChasRole
alaStackMgrChasRole.description: The current role of the chassis as follows: - unassigned(0), - primary(1), - secondary(2), - idle(3), - standalone(4), - passthrough(5).

alaStackMgrLocalLinkStateA.name: alaStackMgrLocalLinkStateA
alaStackMgrLocalLinkStateA.description: 1 indicates that the stacking link A is up, which means it knows its adjacent node. 2 indicates that the stacking link A is inactive and RemoteNISlotA and RemoteLinkA are not significants.

alaStackMgrRemoteNISlotA.name: alaStackMgrRemoteNISlotA
alaStackMgrRemoteNISlotA.description: This is the remote NI slot seen by the current NI through its stacking link A. The numbers allocated for the Stack NIs are 1..8, 1001..1008 or 0 if not present

alaStackMgrRemoteLinkA.name: alaStackMgrRemoteLinkA
alaStackMgrRemoteLinkA.description: This is the remote link of the remote NI slot seen through the stacking link A. The values for these ports are platform dependent. The possible values are: - 0: not present - linkA: 25, 27, 29, 31 or 51 - linkB: 26, 28, 30, 32 or 52.

alaStackMgrLocalLinkStateB.name: alaStackMgrLocalLinkStateB
alaStackMgrLocalLinkStateB.description: 1 indicates that the stacking link B is up, which means it knows its adjacent node. 2 indicates that the stacking link B is inactive and RemoteNISlotB and RemoteLinkB are not significants.

alaStackMgrRemoteNISlotB.name: alaStackMgrRemoteNISlotB
alaStackMgrRemoteNISlotB.description: This is the remote NI slot seen by the current NI through its stacking link B. The numbers allocated for the Stack NIs are 1..8, 1001..1008 or 0 if not present

alaStackMgrRemoteLinkB.name: alaStackMgrRemoteLinkB
alaStackMgrRemoteLinkB.description: This is the remote link of the remote NI slot seen through the stacking link B. The values for these ports are platform dependent. The possible values are: - 0: not present - linkA: 25, 27, 29, 31 or 51 - linkB: 26, 28, 30, 32 or 52.

alaStackMgrChasState.name: alaStackMgrChasState
alaStackMgrChasState.description: This current state of the chassis: running (1), duplicateSlot (2), clearedSlot (3), outOfSlots (4), outOfTokens (5), or badMix (6).

alaStackMgrSavedSlotNINumber.name: alaStackMgrSavedSlotNINumber
alaStackMgrSavedSlotNINumber.description: Slot number stored in persistent memory that will be in effect if the stack element reboots. Only slot numbers in the range 1..8 are allowed.

alaStackMgrCommandAction.name: alaStackMgrCommandAction
alaStackMgrCommandAction.description: This object identifies which of the following Actions is to be performed: clearSlot(1), clearSlotImmediately (2) or reload (3). Whenever a new command is received, the value of the object alaStackMgrCommandStatus will be updated accordingly.

alaStackMgrCommandStatus.name: alaStackMgrCommandStatus
alaStackMgrCommandStatus.description: This object provides the current status of last command received from the management as follows: notSignificant(0), clearSlotInProgress(1), clearSlotFailed(2), clearSlotSuccess(3), setSlotInProgress(4), setSlotFailed(5) or setSlotSuccess(6). New commands are only accepted if the value of this object is different than setSlotInProgress and clearSlotInProgress.

alaStackMgrOperStackingMode.name: alaStackMgrOperStackingMode
alaStackMgrOperStackingMode.description: This object specifies the current running mode of the switch.

alaStackMgrAdminStackingMode.name: alaStackMgrAdminStackingMode
alaStackMgrAdminStackingMode.description: This object specifies the stack mode atained on reload.

alaStackMgrStatLinkNumber.name: alaStackMgrStatLinkNumber
alaStackMgrStatLinkNumber.description: Local link refers to the stacking port on each slot. The values of these ports are: - linkA: 25, 27, 29, 31 or 51 - linkB: 26, 28, 30, 32 or 52.

alaStackMgrStatPktsRx.name: alaStackMgrStatPktsRx
alaStackMgrStatPktsRx.description: The total number of packets recieved on this port.

alaStackMgrStatPktsTx.name: alaStackMgrStatPktsTx
alaStackMgrStatPktsTx.description: The total number of packets transmitted on this port.

alaStackMgrStatErrorsRx.name: alaStackMgrStatErrorsRx
alaStackMgrStatErrorsRx.description: The total number of packets in error - received on the port.

alaStackMgrStatErrorsTx.name: alaStackMgrStatErrorsTx
alaStackMgrStatErrorsTx.description: The total number of packets in error - transmitted on the port.

alaStackMgrStatDelayFromLastMsg.name: alaStackMgrStatDelayFromLastMsg
alaStackMgrStatDelayFromLastMsg.description: The delay since the last message.

alaStackMgrStackStatus.name: alaStackMgrStackStatus
alaStackMgrStackStatus.description: Indicates whether the Stack is or not in Loop.

alaStackMgrTokensUsed.name: alaStackMgrTokensUsed
alaStackMgrTokensUsed.description: Indicates the total number of tokens that have been allocated to all the elements in the stack.

alaStackMgrTokensAvailable.name: alaStackMgrTokensAvailable
alaStackMgrTokensAvailable.description: Indicates the total number of tokens that are still available and that potentially may be allocated to elements of the stack.

alaStackMgrStaticRouteTable.name: alaStackMgrStaticRouteTable
alaStackMgrStaticRouteTable.description: Maintains a list with information about all the static routes in the stack.

alaStackMgrStaticRouteEntry.name: alaStackMgrStaticRouteEntry
alaStackMgrStaticRouteEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to a static route and lists its source and destination in the stack.

alaStackMgrStaticRouteSrcStartIf.name: alaStackMgrStaticRouteSrcStartIf
alaStackMgrStaticRouteSrcStartIf.description: The physical identification number for start source range of the static route

alaStackMgrStaticRouteSrcEndIf.name: alaStackMgrStaticRouteSrcEndIf
alaStackMgrStaticRouteSrcEndIf.description: The physical identification number for end source range of the static route

alaStackMgrStaticRouteDstStartIf.name: alaStackMgrStaticRouteDstStartIf
alaStackMgrStaticRouteDstStartIf.description: The physical identification number for start destination range of the static route

alaStackMgrStaticRouteDstEndIf.name: alaStackMgrStaticRouteDstEndIf
alaStackMgrStaticRouteDstEndIf.description: The physical identification number for end destination range of the static route

alaStackMgrStaticRoutePort.name: alaStackMgrStaticRoutePort
alaStackMgrStaticRoutePort.description: This is the stack link to the destination NI slot . The values for these ports are platform dependent. The possible values are: - 0: not present - linkA: 25, 27, 29, 31 or 51 - linkB: 26, 28, 30, 32 or 52. Incase of static routesthe value is either 1(STACKA) or 2(STACKB)

alaStackMgrStaticRoutePortState.name: alaStackMgrStaticRoutePortState
alaStackMgrStaticRoutePortState.description: 1 indicates that the static route stacking link is up . 2 indicates that the stacking link is inactive.

alaStackMgrStaticRouteStatus.name: alaStackMgrStaticRouteStatus
alaStackMgrStaticRouteStatus.description: Whether this static route is enabled or disabled .

alaStackMgrStaticRouteRowStatus.name: alaStackMgrStaticRouteRowStatus
alaStackMgrStaticRouteRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

alaStackMgrTrapLinkNumber.name: alaStackMgrTrapLinkNumber
alaStackMgrTrapLinkNumber.description: Holds the link number, when the stack is not in loop.

alaStackMgrPrimary.name: alaStackMgrPrimary
alaStackMgrPrimary.description: Holds the slot number of the stack element that plays the role of Primary.

alaStackMgrSecondary.name: alaStackMgrSecondary
alaStackMgrSecondary.description: Holds the slot number of the stack element that plays the role of Secondary.

alaStackMgrDuplicateSlotTrap.name: alaStackMgrDuplicateSlotTrap
alaStackMgrDuplicateSlotTrap.description: The element specified by alaStackMgrSlotNINumber has the same slot number of another element of the stack and it must relinquish its operational status because it has a higher election key (up time, slot, mac). The elements will be put in pass through mode.

alaStackMgrNeighborChangeTrap.name: alaStackMgrNeighborChangeTrap
alaStackMgrNeighborChangeTrap.description: Indicates whether the stack is in loop or not. In case of no loop, alaStackMgrSlotNINumber and alaStackMgrTrapLinkNumber indicate where the Stack is broken

alaStackMgrRoleChangeTrap.name: alaStackMgrRoleChangeTrap
alaStackMgrRoleChangeTrap.description: Role Change Trap. Indicates that a new primary or secondary is elected.

alaStackMgrDuplicateRoleTrap.name: alaStackMgrDuplicateRoleTrap
alaStackMgrDuplicateRoleTrap.description: The element identified by alaStackMgrSlotNINumber detected the presence of two elements with the same primary or secondary role as specified by alaStackMgrChasRole on the stack.

alaStackMgrClearedSlotTrap.name: alaStackMgrClearedSlotTrap
alaStackMgrClearedSlotTrap.description: The element identified by alaStackMgrSlotNINumber will enter the pass through mode because its operational slot was cleared with immediate effect.

alaStackMgrOutOfSlotsTrap.name: alaStackMgrOutOfSlotsTrap
alaStackMgrOutOfSlotsTrap.description: One element of the stack will enter the pass through mode because there are no slot numbers available to be assigned to this element.

alaStackMgrOutOfTokensTrap.name: alaStackMgrOutOfTokensTrap
alaStackMgrOutOfTokensTrap.description: The element identified by alaStackMgrSlotNINumber will enter the pass through mode because there are no tokens available to be assigned to this element.

alaStackMgrOutOfPassThruSlotsTrap.name: alaStackMgrOutOfPassThruSlotsTrap
alaStackMgrOutOfPassThruSlotsTrap.description: There are no pass through slots available to be assigned to an element that is supposed to enter the pass through mode.

alaStackMgrBadMixTrap.name: alaStackMgrBadMixTrap
alaStackMgrBadMixTrap.description: The element identified by alaStackMgrSlotNINumber will enter the pass through mode because it is not compatible with the existing stack.

alaStackMgrCfgMgrGroup.name: alaStackMgrCfgMgrGroup
alaStackMgrCfgMgrGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about the topology of the stack .

alaStackMgrNotificationGroup.name: alaStackMgrNotificationGroup
alaStackMgrNotificationGroup.description: A collection of notifications for signaling Stack manager events.

alcatelIND1StackMgrMIBCompliance.name: alcatelIND1StackMgrMIBCompliance
alcatelIND1StackMgrMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for device support of Stack Manager.
